videos.description: Destiny Littleton comes off the screen and splashes the 3-pointer.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Littleton splashes 3 for South Carolina) 2021/12/30 ESHEET

videos.headline: Littleton splashes 3 for South Carolina

videos.description: Missouri's Hayley Frank bottoms the 3-pointer, putting the Tigers up eight late in the first half.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Frank buries 3, putting Missouri up 8 in the first half) 2021/12/30 ESHEET

videos.headline: Frank buries 3, putting Missouri up 8 in the first half

videos.description: Missouri guard Hayley Frank puts on a series of moves to get the defender off balanced for the and-1.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Frank puts on the moves for impressive Missouri and-1) 2021/12/30 ESHEET

videos.headline: Frank puts on the moves for impressive Missouri and-1

videos.description: South Carolina's Zia Cooke almost puts in the game-winning floater at the buzzer but it rims out sending game to overtime.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Cooke nearly wins it at the buzzer for South Carolina) 2021/12/30 ESHEET

videos.headline: Cooke nearly wins it at the buzzer for South Carolina

videos.description: Missouri's Lauren Hansen makes the layup with less than a second remaining, giving the Tigers the upset win over No. 1 South Carolina.

tracking.trackingName: NCW_One-Play (Missouri’s Hansen sinks layup in final second knocking off No. 1 South Carolina) 2021/12/30 ESHEET

videos.headline: Missouri's Hansen sinks layup in final second knocking off No. 1 South Carolina

videos.description: Following Missouri's first program win against a top-seeded team, Robin Pingeton breaks down the game-winning play to defeat No. 1 South Carolina in OT, 70-69.
videos.headline: Pingeton details final play in Mizzou's historic win
